quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,When heaven will split asunder
  84,2,obeying her Lord’s command as she ought to
  84,3,When the earth will spread out
  84,4,and cast out all that is within her and becomes empty
  84,5,obeying her Lord’s command as she ought to
  84,6,"O mankind! Surely you must strive towards your Lord, a hard striving, then you shall meet Him"
  84,7,Then he who will be given his Book of deeds in his right hand
  84,8,shall have a quick and easy reckoning
  84,9,and shall return to his people rejoicing
  84,10,But he who will be given his book of deeds from behind his back
  84,11,shall soon be calling for death
  84,12,and shall be made to enter a blazing fire
  84,13,for he used to live happily with his kinfolks
  84,14,and thought that he would never return to Allah for accountability
  84,15,"Yet, surely his Lord was ever watching"
  84,16,I swear by the glow of sunset
  84,17,by the night and all that it gathers together
  84,18,"by the moon, when she grows full"
  84,19,that you shall gradually pass from one stage to another
  84,20,What is the matter with the people that they do not believe
  84,21,"and when the Qur’an is recited to them, they do not prostrate"
  84,22,Nay! The unbelievers will deny
  84,23,and Allah knows what they are hiding in their hearts
  84,24,"Therefore, proclaim to them a painful punishment"
  84,25,except those who embrace the true faith and do good deeds; for them there will be a never ending reward
  85,1,By the heaven and its constellations
  85,2,By the promised Day of Judgment
  85,3,By the witnesses and that which is being witnessed
  85,4,Doomed be the makers of the ditch
  85,5,who lit the fuel-fed fire
  85,6,and sat around it
  85,7,to watch what they were doing to the believers
  85,8,"They tortured them for no other reason than that they believed in Allah, the All-Mighty, the Praise Worthy"
  85,9,"the One to Whom belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and earth, and Allah is Witness to all things"
  85,10,"Those who persecute the believing men and believing women and do not repent, shall receive the punishment of hell, wherein they shall have the punishment of conflagration"
  85,11,"As for those who believe and do good deeds, they shall have gardens beneath which rivers flow; which will be the greatest success"
  85,12,"Surely, the seizure of your Lord is very severe"
  85,13,"Surely, He it is Who originates the creation of everything, and He it is Who will repeat it on the Day of Resurrection"
  85,14,"He is the Forgiving, the Loving"
  85,15,"the Owner of the Throne, the Glorious"
  85,16,and the executor of His own will
  85,17,Have you not heard the story of the warriors
  85,18,of Pharaoh and of Thamud
  85,19,Yet the unbelievers persist in denying the truth
  85,20,although Allah has encircled them from all around
  85,21,Surely this is a Glorious Qur’an
  85,22,inscribed on an Imperishable Tablet
  86,1,By the heaven and by the morning star (visitant by night)
  86,2,and what will explain to you what the visitant by night is
  86,3,It is the star of piercing brightness
  86,4,"(Just as Allah Almighty is taking care of each star in the galaxies, similarly) over each soul there is an appointed guardian angel"
  86,5,Let man consider from what he is created
  86,6,He is created from an emitted fluid
  86,7,that is produced from between the loins and the ribs
  86,8,"Surely He, the Creator, has the power to bring him back to life"
  86,9,on the Day when the hidden secrets will be brought to scrutiny
  86,10,then he will have neither power of his own nor any helper to save him from the punishment of Allah
  86,11,By the sky which sends down rain
  86,12,and by the earth which is ever bursting with new growth
  86,13,surely this Qur’an is a decisive word
  86,14,and it is no joke
  86,15,These unbelievers of Mecca are plotting a scheme
  86,16,"and I, too, am plotting a scheme"
  86,17,"Therefore, leave the unbelievers alone. Leave them alone for a while"